\f0\b\fs64 \cf0 Ginger Lemonade
\f1\b0\fs48 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\ql\qnatural

\fs40 \cf0 Serves:  8 servings
\fs38 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs56 \cf0 Ingredients
\f1\b0\fs54 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\ql\qnatural
\cf0 2/3 cup sugar\
2 tablespoon grated ginger\
4 large strips lemon peel\
Juice of 4 lemons\
Ice, for serving\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs56 \cf0 Directions
\f1\b0\fs54 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\ql\qnatural
\cf0 Combine the sugar, ginger and lemon peel in a small saucepot. Pour enough water to cover the mixture, about 2 cups. Bring the mixture to a boil and simmer, about 5 minutes. Remove the saucepot from the heat and let sit at least 15 minutes up to a few hours.\
Pour the lemon juice in a pitcher. Add 6 cups water and the sugar mixture and mix to combine. Serve the lemonade over ice.\
